// test/sema/s07/fail_seq.nsl — S7 (lang.ebnf:850) fail variant.
// A `seq { }` block at module scope (outside a func/proc body)
// violates S7.
//
// Frozen diagnostic per `contracts/diagnostic-string.contract.md`:
//   'seq' block may appear only inside a function or procedure body (S7)
//
// FixItHint per `diagnostic-string.contract.md` table (T040,
// when removable): replaceRange = SeqBlock::seqKwAndBracesRange,
// replacement = `<stripped contents>`.
//
// **Phase 4a TDD red state**: no S7 checker exists; FAILS until
// Phase 4b T048.

// RUN: not %nslc -emit=ast %s 2>&1 | FileCheck %s

module m_fail {
  seq { }
}

// CHECK: error: 'seq' block may appear only inside a function or procedure body (S7)
// (No fix-it asserted: the locked S7 message is informational.
// A precise fix-it would need to preserve the `seq` block's body
// while stripping the keyword + braces, but M2's SeqBlock AST
// doesn't carry separate ranges for those tokens. See Copilot
// review PR#8 line 33 for the rationale.)
